notes.body_html:
Hi,
 
Greetings from PharmEasy.
 
This email is with reference to your query about the Incorrect invoice for order #650569549634920448-25467
 
We are sorry to inform you that as per our process, we are unable to provide you the modified invoice, as the patient name was updated by you at the time of placing the order

OR

We are sorry to inform you that as per our process,we are unable to mention the Dr name on invoice for Prescription not required medicines.
 
For any further assistance, please reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the "Need Help" section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

I am writing to you on behalf of Grey Matters, The Quiz Society, Delhi Public School Vasant Kunj. We are hosting the premier Grey Matters Annual Inter-School Quiz scheduled tentatively for December 19th, 2025.

notes.body: Hello B. Jayanth,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9705001202 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well.      Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.      Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal

helpdesk_ticket.description:
I had placed an order for a bottle of Ever Herb Karela with Pharmeasy on
13th November along with other medicines. I received the package today
evening. I was shocked and surprised to see the bottle half empty. When I
physically counted the capsules, I found that the bottle contained only 47
capsules instead of 60 as mentioned on the label. The batch Number is
TLH004 and Mfg. Date is August 2025. This is a clear case of cheating. I am
a retired pensioner and paying a big sum of Rs.600 per bottle.

I have raised this issue on telephone with Pharmeasy customer care as well
as Ever Herb customer service.

Please look into the matter and respond immediately, failing which I will
be compelled to raise this issue on other forums or platforms.

Sudhish Nayar

notes.body: Hello Subhodeep,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9635243192 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well.      Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.      Please be informed that we are unable to comply with his request to erase the data. We have to produce/show any or all transactions or interactions, past or present, when asked for by relevant government authorities. However, please confirm if you wish to deactivate your account.     Let me inform you that once the account is deactivated, we cannot process any requests or reactivate the account. Once confirmed, our team will reach out to complete the account deactivation process on the registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation.      If yes, OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you with the team, they will go ahead and block the customer's account.     Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal
notes.body_html:

Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.

Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number 9635243192 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual sim phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well. 

Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.

I certainly hope this helps and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile. 

Please be informed that we are unable to comply with his request to erase the data. We have to produce/show any or all transactions or interactions, past or present, when asked for by relevant government authorities. However, please confirm if you wish to deactivate your account.
 
Let me inform you that once the account is deactivated, we cannot process any requests or reactivate the account. Once confirmed, our team will reach out to complete the account deactivation process on the registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation. 

If yes, OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you with the team, they will go ahead and block the customer's account.

Awaiting your response.

Regards,
Sandhya Nackwal

notes.body: Hello Kannan,      Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to promotional SMS, we always try to keep our customers updated on our offers. However, we apologize for the inconvenience caused due to our promotional messages.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your numbers 9894640285 and 8838410939 from receiving promotional SMS. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. Also, if you have a dual SIM phone, I would request you to help us with the second number as well. We will forward a request for the other number as well.      Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email ID too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.     I certainly hope this helps and appreciate your understanding and patience in the meanwhile.      Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal

notes.body: Hello Anil,       Greetings from PharmEasy!     Please be informed that we are unable to comply with his request to erase the data. We have to produce/show any or all transactions or interactions, past or present, when asked for by relevant government authorities. However, please confirm if you wish to deactivate your account.     Let me inform you that once the account is deactivated, we cannot process any requests or reactivate the account. Once confirmed, our team will reach out to complete the account deactivation process on the registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation.      If yes, OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you with the team, they will go ahead and block the customer's account.      Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal

Merged from ticket 22251330  
      Subject: Urgent: Extremely Delayed Delivery - Order ID 652573802194456576 - Tracking ID 9148880965543  
      Description:  
 Dear PharmEasy Customer Care Team, 
 I am writing to express my extreme disappointment and frustration regarding my order that has been significantly delayed beyond the promised delivery date. 
 Order Details: 
 
 Order ID: 652573802194456576-36159-HOG 
 Tracking ID: 9148880965543 
 Courier Partner: Delhivery 
 Expected Delivery: November 30 - December 1, 2024 
 Current Status: Still in transit (Last update: December 3) 
 
 My order was supposed to be delivered between November 30 and December 1, but as of today (December 4), it has still not been delivered. What is even more shocking and unacceptable is the bizarre routing of my shipment: 
 
 
Shipped from: Ambala, Haryana (November 26) 
 
My delivery location: Agra, Uttar Pradesh 
 
Actual shipment route: The package traveled to Chandigarh/Punjab, then incredibly went all the way to Bangalore, Karnataka, and now I have no idea where it currently is 
 
 This is absolutely ridiculous! My order was supposed to be delivered in Agra, UP - a straightforward route from Ambala, Haryana (approximately 400-500 km). Instead, it has been sent across the country in completely wrong directions - first to Punjab, then inexplicably all the way to Bangalore in South India (over 2,000 km in the opposite direction). This makes no logistical sense whatsoever and suggests a serious failure in Delhivery's routing system. 
 This is completely unacceptable, especially considering that medicines and healthcare products are often time-sensitive and urgently needed. The misrouting of my shipment and complete lack of clarity on its current whereabouts is causing significant inconvenience and distress. 
 
To make matters worse, I have been trying to reach your customer service through both chat and phone calls, but I am unable to connect with an actual human representative. Your AI chatbot keeps responding with generic "I can help you with this and that" messages but provides no real solution or human assistance. This is extremely frustrating when I have such a serious issue that clearly requires human intervention and immediate action. 
 
I am a PharmEasy Plus member, and I expected priority service and better delivery standards as part of my paid membership. Instead, I am facing the worst possible service - a completely misrouted shipment, no clarity on delivery, and no access to human customer support. This is a complete failure of the premium service I paid for. 
 I request the following immediate actions: 
 
 An explanation for this severe delay 
 The current exact location of my shipment 
 A confirmed delivery date and time 
 Compensation for the inconvenience caused due to this delay 
 
 I have been a customer of PharmEasy and expected better service standards. This experience has been extremely disappointing, and I hope this matter will be resolved urgently. 
 I look forward to your prompt response and immediate action on this matter. 
 
Contact Details:
 Deepak Sharma
 Phone: +91 8273738488
 Email: dsharma2828@gmail.com  
 
 Regards,
 Deepak Sharma
